<div id="review_3610247890" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3610247890" />
    <a title="Cait M" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/96903733-cait-m"><img alt="Cait M" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611646115p2/96903733.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3610247890?book_show_action=true">Oct 24, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cait M" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cait M" href="/user/show/96903733-cait-m">Cait M</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3610247890" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13228705778154251155">Clarissa Kae has produced a debut novel that ticks a lot of boxes and kept me turning pages until well into the night.<br/>She has created an intricate world where many time-lines appear to intersect. The hero Rhys has a very extended life span and the heroine is Isla Belle, Rhys&apos; wife who appears in his life in many iterations throughout the years.<br/><br/>Modern-day Isla Belle is an American whose mother has a history of mental illness. When Isla&apos;s dreams of a blonde man start to invade her waking hours, re</span>
  <span id="freeText13228705778154251155" style="display:none">Clarissa Kae has produced a debut novel that ticks a lot of boxes and kept me turning pages until well into the night.<br />She has created an intricate world where many time-lines appear to intersect. The hero Rhys has a very extended life span and the heroine is Isla Belle, Rhys' wife who appears in his life in many iterations throughout the years.<br /><br />Modern-day Isla Belle is an American whose mother has a history of mental illness. When Isla's dreams of a blonde man start to invade her waking hours, resulting in vivid visions followed by crushing headaches, she fears she is losing her grip on reality too.<br /><br />I enjoyed the creativity of the storyline, although there were times when I was a little confused as to who was who. This is a clean romance. There is a cliff-hanger ending and the next book in the series "Disorder in the Veins" is unavailable as of yet. <br /><br />I am unsure how many books it would take to tell the story of all the various lifetimes Isla Belle has had so far. Hopefully no more than 3 because I admit my preference is always for a HEA at the end of a book and that is not quite the case here. A trilogy is definately my limit for a story arc between 2 characters.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13228705778154251155" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


