  <span id="freeText7657215369675329050" style="display:none">This story was fascinating as it not only explored the realms of immortality and reincarnation but also mental illness. The modern day Isla Belle struggles with the visions in her head - or are they memories? Controlled and frightened by the mysterious Denton and his clinic and her over-protective uncle, and overwhelmed by the burden of her mother's mental health and drug addiction, she fears she is just like her, but gradually unravels the secrets surrounding her, and within her own head, to discover a love that is timeless. But what of Rhys? His loneliness and heartache, and the lengths he will go to, to reunite with his wife are painful and heart-rending. There is a lot left unsaid that hopefully will be revealed in Book 2.</span>
